article.headline: Missouri St. 65, Evansville 62
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. -- Chris Cooks had 18 points and 10 rebounds to lead Missouri State to 65-62 comeback win over Evansville on Wednesday night. Will Creekmore added 11 points for the Bears (10-13, 3-9 Missouri Valley), including seven straight points in a 20-7 second-half run that tied the game at 53. The two teams traded baskets for several minutes before Cooks made two free throws and a field goal to put Missouri State ahead for good 61-57 with 2:32 left. Evansville (14-8, 6-6) broke open a 30-all halftime tie with a 16-3 run capped by a Jason Holsinger field goal. Nate Gardner finished with 24 points and 11 rebounds for the Aces. Gardner scored seven of Evansville's first 16 points in the second half, but was held to one point in the final 10:32. Shy Ely added 15 points and Zach House had 10 for Evansville.
